description:
ThinkGeo.MapSuite.Layers.Grids is a layer extension to the Map Suite product line, see below for compatibility.  This extension provides the ability to load grids and render on maps.

The layer displays cells with different colors in a rectangular area of a map. The color of a cell depends on the cell value in the grid file. The grid file provides information about the grid such as row and column numbers, coordinates of the lower left corner, cell size, and values of cells.  

** This is an extension for use in ThinkGeo's Map Suite product line, see below,  as it cannot be used stand alone. **

Wiki Documentation: http://wiki.thinkgeo.com/wiki/map_suite_api

Supported Platforms: Windows, Linux, macOS, iOS, Android

- Compatible Products -
    Map Suite Desktop for WPF
    Map Suite Desktop for WinForms
    Map Suite Mobile for Android
    Map Suite Mobile for iOS
    Map Suite Web for WebForms
    Map Suite Web for MVC
    Map Suite Web for WebAPI

This package can be used to easily run a unit test project using the .NET Memory Profiler tool NmpCore after the build of a project.
It is suitable to be used together with the .NET Memory Profiler API (SciTech.MemProfilerApi), which can be used to perform memory assertions, retrieve memory usage, and collect memory snapshots.
After installing the package, select "NmpCore" as build action for the file "ProfileTest.prfproj".
For more information, see https://memprofiler.com/nmpcore, and https://memprofiler.com/apiexamples.
summary: This package extends the NmpCore Task package with a .NET Memory Profiler project that is automatically run using NmpCore after build.

description:
The NmpCore Task can be used to easily run the .NET Memory Profiler tool NmpCore after the build of a project, for example a unit test project that uses the .NET Memory Profiler API (SciTech.MemProfilerApi).
To include a sample .NET Memory Profiler project that automatically runs unit test after build, use the package SciTech.NmpCore.TestProject instead.
For more information, see https://memprofiler.com/nmpcore, and https://memprofiler.com/apiexamples.
summary: The NmpCore Task can be used to easily run the NmpCore tool after the build of a project, for example a unit test project that uses the .NET Memory Profiler API.

description:
The .NET Memory Profiler API can be used to retrieve memory usage information, perform memory assertions, and collect memory snapshots from within a profiled process.
This API is intended to be used for automatic memory testing with the help of .NET Memory Profiler or NmpCore.
The SciTech.NmpCore.TestProject package can be used to easily run a unit test library using NmpCore.
For more information, see http://memprofiler.com/, http://memprofiler.com/nmpcore.aspx, and http://memprofiler.com/apiexamples.aspx.
Note that this API requires .NET Memory Profiler or NmpCore version 5.5 (beta) or later.
summary: API library for .NET Memory Profiler and NmpCore.
